edu.metrostate.ics372.thatgroup.clinicaltrial.importexport

Class TrialDataJsonImportExporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.metrostate.ics372.thatgroup.clinicaltrial.importexport.TrialDataJsonImportExporter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TrialDataExporter, TrialDataImporter

    public class TrialDataJsonImportExporter
extends java.lang.Object
implements TrialDataImporter, TrialDataExporter
    The TrialDataJsonImportExporter is used for importing and exporting trial data to and from a JSON file. It includes methods to read from a JSON file and write to a JSON file.
    Author:
    That Group

      • read

        public boolean read(Trial trial,
                    java.io.InputStream is)
             throws TrialException
        Reads the specified JSON file and returns true if the import was successful. If the import was successful, then the lists for the imported objects will be valid after this method returns.
        Specified by:
        read in interface TrialDataImporter
        Parameters:
        trial - the trial that the data is being imported into. Cannot be null.
        is - the ImportStream to read the data from.
        Returns:
        true if the import was successful; otherwise false is returned.
        Throws:
        TrialException - indicates an error occurred while operating on the file.
